
                        Section 2 - Notes
                      ENTRYPOINT Instruction

1.  Dockerfile in this directory.

    $ cat Dockerfile
    FROM busybox
    ENTRYPOINT ["/bin/head", "-5"]
    CMD ["/etc/passwd"]

2.  Build image.

    $ docker build -t head .

3.  Run container with default entry point.

    $ docker run head
    root:x:0:0:root:/root:/bin/sh
    daemon:x:1:1:daemon:/usr/sbin:/bin/false
    bin:x:2:2:bin:/bin:/bin/false
    sys:x:3:3:sys:/dev:/bin/false
    sync:x:4:100:sync:/bin:/bin/sync

4.  Run container with entry point from command line.

    $ docker run head /etc/group
    root:x:0:
    daemon:x:1:
    bin:x:2:
    sys:x:3:
    adm:x:4:

